# hi! this is how I learnt to do hard things in simple form: Using shortcuts.

+ **How to write a text into multiple files** \n
Using *echo `sample text` | tee file1 file2 file3* \n
writes `sample text` into `file1`, `file2` and `file3` at the same time.

+ **How to check the first line statement of each file in a directory** \n
head -n 1 *

